      "id": "1204405442749298",
      "score": 4,
      "review_title": "Need more blood",
      "review_description": "The game really entertained me for a few minutes, but then it starts to get boring. I know it's a new release, it came out just a few minutes ago, and in my honest opinion, the game is okay, but it needs improvements with updates and more content, like a menu system, settings, more realistic gore if that's what the game is about, and other things that would require more investment",
      "date": 1778902699,
      "review_helpful_count": 96,
      "author_display_name": "HNC15",
      "author_alias": "HNC15",
      "developer_response": null
    },
    {
      "id": "919060511187320",
      "score": 5,
      "review_title": "All these other reviews are dumb,",
      "review_description": "Sure, the games lacking but it’s not supposed to be like the other Gore games, your working in FRANKENSTEIN, he doesn’t scream  or yelp when being hurt, there does need a bit more weapons though. You can swap out the hearts and brains for ones you find through the small warehouse and eventually the graveyard. Overall great game! Great physics too.",
      "date": 1779246744,
      "review_helpful_count": 24,
      "author_display_name": "neo4321",
      "author_alias": "neo4321",
      "developer_response": null
    },
    {
      "id": "1161596017029347",
      "score": 3,
      "review_title": "Not bad",
      "review_description": "I can't really complain too much since it's a free game, but it's supposed to be all about gore and, well, it's a bit lacking compared to games like Hard Bullet and Blade and Sorcery Nomad. The gore just doesn't quite measure up. Still, as a free option, it's not too bad. I wouldn't mind if they decided to start charging for it to improve it, to be honest. It could definitely use better graphics, fewer lags, and more realistic gore and blood effects. The blood looks fake and the deformations are just not believable. The NPCs don't react at all, and when I try to hit them sometimes their bodies glitch out.",
      "date": 1778919949,
      "review_helpful_count": 5,
      "author_display_name": "gatsu016",
      "author_alias": "gatsu016",
      "developer_response": null
    },
